  "text": "The Kafka Connect REST API is implemented primarily through the ConnectorsResource class at connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/resources/ConnectorsResource.java, which serves as the main JAX-RS resource handler for connector management endpoints. This resource implements handlers for connector creation, configuration, status retrieval, and task management.\n\nThe key response schemas for task and connector status are defined in ConnectorStateInfo.java (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/entities/ConnectorStateInfo.java), which contains nested classes for TaskState and ConnectorState that represent the current state of tasks and connectors respectively. Each includes fields for state (RUNNING, PAUSED, FAILED, etc.), worker_id, trace messages, and version information.\n\nError responses are handled through the ErrorMessage class (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/entities/ErrorMessage.java) which provides a standard format with error_code and message fields, generated automatically by ConnectExceptionMapper.\n\nThe ConnectRestServer class (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/ConnectRestServer.java) provides the routing logic that registers all REST resources, including ConnectorsResource, ConnectorPluginsResource, InternalConnectResource, and other handlers.\n\nStorage schema versioning is evident in KafkaConfigBackingStore.java which defines TARGET_STATE_V0 and TARGET_STATE_V1 schemas, with V1 adding an optional 'state.v2' field for supporting new state values. This suggests internal schema evolution for configuration storage.\n\nThe task status workflow flows through: ConnectorsResource.getTaskStatus() -> Herder.taskStatus() -> ConnectorStateInfo.TaskState, where TaskState is the REST API response schema containing id, state, worker_id, and optional message/trace fields.\n\nWhile explicit v1 and v2 REST API endpoint versions are not found as separate resource classes in the current implementation, the codebase shows version-aware schema evolution in storage layers (V0/V1 schemas) and comprehensive error handling mechanisms for API responses."
}

